Source: Arab News, Sat 7 Oct 2000 [edited

Rift Valley fever in Saudi Arabia: Update
-----------------------------------------
On Sat Oct 7 2000, a Health Ministry Official stated that the death toll
[in the Rift Valley fever outbreak in Saudi Arabia had reached 58, with
affected people totalling 264. A total of 6 new cases of Rift Valley fever
were reported within the last 24 hours.There have also been reports of the
deaths of [a number of sheep in Abha over the past days with disposal of
the carcasses in areas located behind the vegetable and sheep markets.
Samples collected from the dead sheep have been sent to the Agriculture
Ministry's laboratory in Riyadh for testing.
--
Dr.Shamsudeen Fagbo, DVM
<oloungbo@zajil.net>
